            <div type="translation" resp="part:emfr">
                
                <p n="1">Prosperity! Fortune!</p>
                <p n="1">Fourteenth year of the king Parakesarivarman.</p>
                <p n="1-3">I, Mayimālai Irukkuvēḷ,                
                    I have given
                    for the lord of Tirumutukuṉṟam in Koṭumpāḷūr
                    <supplied reason="subaudible">the land named</supplied> <foreign>30 vāy maṅkaḷam</foreign>
                    after 
                    having it cleared from stone <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>nāvi</foreign></supplied>,
                    having it ... <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>curukki</foreign></supplied>,
                    having exempted it tax-free,
                    having removed the tenants,
                    and made it a <foreign>devadāna</foreign>.
                </p>
                <p n="3-4">He<note>The temple priest or officer.</note> is due to deliver one <foreign>aḻakku</foreign> as per the trident standard, one <foreign>kuṟuṇi</foreign> of rice, ghee food-offering, and curd food-offering at midday twilight.</p>
                <p n="4">This is under the protection of the honourable Paṉmāheśvarars.</p>
                
